diff-content--login-error: Please login in the upper right corner before copying.
diff-header-description--diverged: The current version of $1 was not found in the history of the primary page $2.
diff-header-description--ok: Page $1 is a localized version of the original $2.
diff-header-description--unlocalized: Page $1 is identical with the original $2, but needs to have some localizations.
diff-header-warnings--dependencies: The following dependencies are not present on the destination site. Copy these pages to $1 and make sure they are linked to other wikis.
diff-header-warnings--diverged: This page was modified by the $1 community. Do not override it unless:
diff-header-warnings--diverged-1: Local, changes were done by mistake and should be reverted
diff-header-warnings--diverged-2: The local changes are now included in the primary page
diff-header-warnings--diverged-3: The local changes are no longer needed
diff-header-warnings--multisite: This page depends on templates or modules that have not been tagged as "multi-site" in Wikidata. Most of the time this means that page $1 is not yet ready for synchronization, and should not have a multi-site type in $2. Alternatively it could also mean that the page was edited to use a new template/module, and that the new page is not enabled for synchronization.
diff-header-warnings--multisite-head: Dependencies are not enabled for synchronization
diff-summary-text--localized: Localizing $1 to use this wiki's template and module names. ([[mw:Special:MyLanguage/WP:TNT|docs]])
diff-summary-text--reset: Resetting page to the current content of $1. ([[mw:Special:MyLanguage/WP:TNT|docs]])
filters-groupby--tooltip: Group the list of copies by...
header-beta--tooltip: Work in progress. Please verify your changes.
header-description: Keep modules and templates the same across wikis and languages. Written by $1
language--tooltip: Click to change the display language
settings-search--tooltip: Search as you type. If disabled, you must press ENTER after entering the search query string. Disable when your computer is not performing fast enough when entering queries.
settings-split--tooltip: Show page comparison side by side (split) or unified.
sync-button--tooltip: Multi-page sync is not yet implemented
table-cell-diverged--tooltip: {{PLURAL:$1|One page has|$1 pages have}} local modifications and must be synchronized individually.
table-cell-hash--tooltip: This hash number represents a unique fingerprint of the current page content. Pages with identical hash have the same content. The hash is computed before the page was localized for this wiki.
table-cell-outdated--tooltip: {{PLURAL:$1|One page is|$1 pages are}} behind the primary and can be synchronized automatically.
table-cell-primary--tooltip: Show primary $1 in a new tab.
table-cell-status--diverged-tooltip: The target page has been modified and cannot be updated automatically.
table-cell-status--ok--tooltip: The target page is up to date with the primary
table-cell-status--outdated-link: Show what changed in the last {{PLURAL:$1|edit|$1 edits}} of the primary $2 in a new tab.
table-cell-status--outdated-tooltip: The target page is behind by {{PLURAL:$1|1 edit|$1 edits}}, and can be updated. Click to see changes.
table-cell-status--unlocalized-tooltip: The target page has exactly the same content as original instead of using localized values, and needs to be updated.
table-cell-unlocalized--tooltip: {{PLURAL:$1|one page is|$1 pages are}} identical to the original. These pages need to be localized because some dependent templates may have different names on that wiki. This can be done automatically.
table-cell-updated--tooltip: {{PLURAL:$1|One page is|$1 pages are}} up to date.
table-externallink--aria: Open external link in a new tab
table-header-diverged--tooltip: Number of pages with local modifications.
table-header-hash--tooltip: The hash number is a unique fingerprint of the page content. Pages with identical hash have the same content. The hash is computed before the page is localized for a wiki.
table-header-outdated--tooltip: Number of pages that has fallen behind with the primary.
table-header-primary--tooltip: Title of the page at mediawiki.org
table-header-site--tooltip: The wiki site where the copied page is located.
table-header-status--tooltip: Show if the copied page is in sync with the original, has fallen behind, or has been modified locally (diverged).
table-header-unlocalized--tooltip: Number of pages that are identical to the original. These pages need to be localized (e.g. rename dependent templates)
table-header-updated--tooltip: Number of up to date pages.
table-header-wikipage--tooltip: Title of the copied page as it appears on the destination wiki.
table-icons-protection--tooltip: Indicate if the page has protection and requires special edit rights.
updatepage-confirm--description-part2: Are you sure you want to do this?
